cose man, from <i>bataille</i> ‘battle’ (from Latin <i>battualia</i>), or a habitational name from (La) Bataille, the name of several places in France, all named as the site of a battle in former times.","West Indian (mainly Haiti): nickname from French <i>bataille</i> ‘battle’ (compare 1 above)."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":27,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705188,"age":36,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When William Battaille of Fawdon was born in 1188, in Fawdon, Northumberland, England, his father, Henry de Bataille, was 30 and his mother, Margelye le Battailleur-Foeden de Cariou Queret, was 29. He married Constance de Flamville before 1215, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1250, in England, at the age of 62, and was buried in England."},"et":{"1188–1250":"1188–1250","1192–1261":"1192–1261","1215–1292":"1215–1292","1158–1207":"1158–1207","1160–1207":"1160–1207","before 1215":"enne 1215","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1158":"1158","1188":"1188","1250":"1250","1261":"1261","1160":"1160","1292":"1292","1192":"1192","um 1203":"umbes 1203","1207":"1207","Fawdon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Fawdon, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Fawdon, Northumberland, England":"Fawdon, Northumberland, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1188–1250":"1188–1250","1192–1261":"1192–1261","1215–1292":"1215–1292","1158–1207":"1158–1207","1160–1207":"1160–1207","before 1215":"ennen vuotta 1215","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1158":"1158","1188":"1188","1250":"1250","1261":"1261","1160":"1160","1292":"1292","1192":"1192","um 1203":"noin 1203","1207":"1207","Fawdon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Fawdon, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Fawdon, Northumberland, England":"Fawdon, Northumberland, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1188–1250":"1188–1250","1192–1261":"1192–1261","1215–1292":"1215–1292","1158–1207":"1158–1207","1160–1207":"1160–1207","before 1215":"avant 1215","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1158":"1158","1188":"1188","1250":"1250","1261":"1261","1160":"1160","1292":"1292","1192":"1192","um 1203":"environ 1203","1207":"1207","Fawdon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Fawdon, Northumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Fawdon, Northumberland, England":"Fawdon, Northumberland, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William Battaille of Fawdon est né en 1188, à Fawdon, Northumberland, Angleterre, son père, Henry de Bataille, avait 30 ans et sa mère, Margelye le Battailleur-Foeden de Cariou Queret, avait 29 ans. Il a épousé Constance de Flamville avant 1215, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1250, à Angleterre, à l’âge de 62 ans, et a été enterré à Angleterre."},"de":{"1188–1250":"1188–1250","1192–1261":"1192–1261","1215–1292":"1215–1292","1158–1207":"1158–1207","1160–1207":"1160–1207","before 1215":"vor 1215","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1158":"1158","1188":"1188","1250":"1250","1261":"1261","1160":"1160","1292":"1292","1192":"1192","um 1203":"um 1203","1207":"1207","Fawdon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Fawdon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","Fawdon, Northumberland, England":"Fawdon, Northumberland, England","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Als William Battaille of Fawdon 1188 in Fawdon, Northumberland, England geboren wurde, war sein Vater Henry de Bataille 30 und seine Mutter Margelye le Battailleur-Foeden de Cariou Queret 29. Er hat vor 1215 in England Constance de Flamville geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb 1250 im Alter von 62 Jahren in England und wurde in England begraben."},"ht":{"1188–1250":"1188–1250","1192–1261":"1192–1261","1215–1292":"1215–1292","1158–1207":"1158–1207","1160–1207":"1160–1207","before 1215":"before 1215","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1158":"1158","1188":"1188","1250":"1250","1261":"1261","1160":"1160","1292":"1292","1192":"1192","um 1203":"about 1203","1207":"1207","Fawdon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Fawdon, Northumberland, Angletè, United Kingdom","Fawdon, Northumberland, England":"Fawdon, Northumberland, England","England":"England"},"hu":{"1188–1250":"1188–1250","1192–1261":"1192–1261","1215–1292":"1215–1292","1158–1207":"1158–1207","1160–1207":"1160–1207","before 1215":"1215 előtt","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1158":"1158","1188":"1188","1250":"1250","1261":"1261","1160":"1160","1292":"1292","1192":"1192","um 1203":"1203 körül","1207":"1207","Fawdon, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Fa